{
  "summary": "This PR adds OTel tracing, cost calculation, and trace persistence features. Most changes are correct, but there are a few concerns: TracingOptions.IncludePrompts defaults to true which could leak prompts in production, TraceCleanupService has a potential file enumeration performance issue for large deployments, and JsonReviewTraceWriter has no temp file cleanup if rename fails. The cost calculation uses decimal arithmetic correctly.",
  "comments": [
    {
      "path": "src/ReviewBot.Api/Tracing/TracingOptions.cs",
      "line": 9,
      "severity": "warning",
      "confidence": "high",
      "body": "IncludePrompts defaults to `true` but should default to `false` for production. This could leak sensitive system prompts in trace files. Set to `false` by default and document that users must explicitly enable prompt inclusion in dev environments."
    },
    {
      "path": "src/ReviewBot.Api/Tracing/JsonReviewTraceWriter.cs",
      "line": 47,
      "severity": "warning",
      "confidence": "high",
      "body": "If `File.Move` fails after writing to the temp file, the `.tmp` file is left behind and never cleaned up. Add a `try/finally` or `using` block to delete the temp file if the rename fails."
    },
    {
      "path": "src/ReviewBot.Api/Tracing/TraceCleanupService.cs",
      "line": 56,
      "severity": "info",
      "confidence": "high",
      "body": "Using `allFiles.Length` for list capacity is unnecessary overhead since the list is empty when created. Remove this initialization to avoid allocating a large array upfront."
    },
    {
      "path": "src/ReviewBot.Api/Tracing/TraceCleanupService.cs",
      "line": 100,
      "severity": "info",
      "confidence": "high",
      "body": "The `TryDelete` method doesn't check if the file exists before attempting deletion. Add a `File.Exists()` check or use `try/catch` to handle `IOException` when the file was already deleted by another process."
    },
    {
      "path": "src/ReviewBot.Api/Tracing/TraceCleanupService.cs",
      "line": 49,
      "severity": "warning",
      "confidence": "medium",
      "body": "This service enumerates all `.json` files recursively under `tracesDir` before deletion. For deployments with many trace files (e.g., thousands), this could cause noticeable CPU spikes. Consider adding a file count limit or batching the deletion operation."
    },
    {
      "path": "src/ReviewBot.Api/Tracing/TracingOptions.cs",
      "line": 11,
      "severity": "info",
      "confidence": "high",
      "body": "MaxDiskMb defaults to 500 which is reasonable but could be tuned per deployment. Document this in the README or add a note in the code about adjusting for cost-sensitive environments."
    }
  ]
}

